underlying_goal: To diagnose and fix duplicate skill listings in Claude Code, and in the process, create a robust cross-tool skill synchronization strategy for Codex and Gemini.
primary_success: Correctly diagnosed that 57 git-tracked symlinks in the user skills directory were causing the duplicate skill listings, and expanded the scope to create a comprehensive cross-tool extensibility map and a robust sync script plan.
brief_summary: The user reported duplicate skills. Claude investigated and found 57 symlinks in the user skills directory pointing to the plugin cache were the cause. The session then expanded to a full analysis of cross-tool extensibility, resulting in a comprehensive 7-part plan to fix the duplicates, create new sync scripts for Gemini and Codex, and document the entire ecosystem.
